    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "valgrind is tough to run on our specific hardware because it's a resource-constrained ARM target, and we can't really afford the overhead during live testing. and asan is also a bit heavy for our production build. \n\nif i can't use heavy instrumentation, what are some more lightweight ways to isolate it? specifically if the leak is occurring in a background thread that only spawns every few hundred cycles? any specific patterns or log-based methods you'd suggest?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
