      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since heavy instrumentation is off the table, I recommend implementing a lightweight custom allocator wrapper that logs heap growth to a non-blocking circular buffer instead of a full trace. For background threads, focus on correlating timestamps between the background spawn rate and the spike in your heap usage statistics to isolate the specific module. You can also add a periodic \"leak check\" routine that resets the heap counter and compares the delta across known intervals to identify if the leak is tied to the thread's execution window.",
